registrable

Interface Registrable<R>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    MultiObjectiveRegistrable, SingleObjectiveRegistrable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PipeOptimizingRegister, PumpSchedulingNSGAIIRegister, PumpSchedulingSMPSORegister, PumpSchedulingSPA2Register

    public interface Registrable<R>
    It is the superinterface to SingleObjectiveRegistrable and MultiObjectiveRegistrable.

    The class that implement this interface has to have a only public constructor that declare the parameters that is needed to configure the experiment and the problem. Also the constructor has to add a series of annotation. Based in the parameters added in the constructor the experiment have to be configured and returned when build(String) will be called.

    The annotation that the constructor has to have are:

    • NewProblem : It annotation is used to assign the name to the problem and the name to the algorithm to use within experiment. It will be showed in the menu in the GUI. It annotation is mandatory.
    • Parameters : It annotation declare that in this constructor will be injected the parameters. It injection is realized from ConfigurationDynamicWindow that is a GUI dynamically built from the parameters that has been configured in this annotation. Each constructor parameters has to be described through their respective annotation. If a constructor parameter don't have an annotation that describe it then an exception will be thrown. Eg. if a parameter of constructor will be a Object so in the parameter annotation has to be a Operator annotation the describe the type of element to inject. The Operator has to be added to Parameters.operators(). This annotation is optional, but if this notation is not in the constructor then the constructor can't have parameters.


    The order and the type in what the constructor params are added is important. The order has to be the next:

    1. Object: The operators will be injected in the parameters of type object. It can be casted to the respective class or superclass. It is described using Parameters.operators()
    2. File: It describe a file that will be injected. Is used if the algorithm need a extra file that has configuration or values. It is described using Parameters.files()
    3. int(or Integer)|double(or Double): It describe a value needed to configure the problem. Eg. the number of iterations, or the number of iteration without improvement. It is described using Parameters.numbers() or Parameters.numbersToggle()

    Parameters has a operators property, files property, numbers property and numberToggle property. The operators property receive OperatorInput, the files property receive FileInput and numbers receive NumberInput and the numberToggle receive NumberToggleInput. OperatorInput denote that a operator will be received and the type of it (Eg. Selection, Mutation, etc). The OperatorInput let one or more OperatorOption that indicate what Operator can be used in this problem.

    FileInput denote a file. it let use files with information to execute the algorithm. If FileInput.type() is FileInput.Type#SAVE it open the FileChooser window in save mode. NumberInput denote a int or a double value that are received by the constructor.

    NumberToggleInput denote a int or a double value that are received by the constructor but it are mutually exclusive if is NumberToggleInput.groupID() are the same.

    A example is showed in the class PipeOptimizingRegister.

    • Method Detail

      • build

        @NotNull
R build(java.lang.String inpPath)
           throws java.lang.Exception
        Builds a new experiment and leaves it ready for execution. This method will be called by the GUI when resolve the problem in the network opened. The call include the path of the inp file of the opened network.
        Parameters:
        inpPath - the path of inp file, or null if there isn't a network opened.
        Returns:
        the experiment ready for execution
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if an exception occurs when building the experiment

      • getParameters

        @Nullable
default @Nullable java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getParameters()
        Return a map where save the value of configuration used.

        This method let add more information to ResultWindow because add new columns with the values added here. The key will be used has the column name and the value as value of column.

        If the map has no value or the method return null. So the ResultWindow only show objectives and the variables.

        Returns:
        the map or null.
